---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout title="Saje Editions - AI Reading Platform">
  <h1 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Saje Editions</h1>
  
  <div class="mb-4">
    <a
      href="https://sajedition.com"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="inline-flex items-center space-x-2 text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300 font-mono font-semibold"
    >
      <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        width="24"
        height="24"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
        class="w-5 h-5"
      >
        <path d="M5 12h14"></path>
        <path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path>
      </svg>
      <span>â†’ sajedition.com</span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-2">Overview</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Saje Editions is an AI-powered reading and publishing platform that transforms PDF and EPUB
    libraries into interactive tutors. Users can upload books, chat with the content, and receive
    grounded answers with citations, summaries, and study aids.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Core Capabilities</h2>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Book Ingestion and Indexing</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    A backend pipeline parses PDF/EPUB files, chunks content, enriches context, and stores embeddings
    in pgvector for fast semantic retrieval.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Hybrid Retrieval and RAG</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Combines vector similarity with BM25 lexical search and reciprocal rank fusion to deliver precise,
    page-cited answers and streaming responses.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Learning Workflows</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Generates summaries, quizzes, and flashcards to help readers revise and retain knowledge without
    leaving the reading flow.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Technology Stack</h2>

  <ul class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Frontend</strong>: Next.js 16, Tailwind CSS</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Backend</strong>: FastAPI with Supabase Auth</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Data</strong>: Supabase Postgres + pgvector</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">AI</strong>: LiteLLM/OpenRouter, Gemini embeddings</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Infra</strong>: Docker Compose, Supabase Storage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Key Challenges</h2>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Retrieval Quality</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Ensuring accurate grounding required hybrid search, contextual chunking, and careful prompt
    design to keep responses tightly aligned with sources.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Document Diversity</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Supporting a wide range of PDFs and EPUBs demanded robust parsing and validation to handle
    formatting edge cases at scale.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Project Impact</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Saje Editions demonstrates how RAG systems can turn static content into interactive learning
    experiences, with a focus on trust, citations, and study utility.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Future Development</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Planned improvements include conversation export, richer study modes, and deeper collaboration
    features for classrooms and teams.
  </p>
</ProjectLayout>
